100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On December 23, 1925, the British Parliament faced heated debates over the future of the country's coal industry, with miners striking for better wages and working conditions amid rising tensions. In Italy, Mussolini's government continued to consolidate power, suppressing opposition and expanding its influence across the nation. Meanwhile, in the United States, the holiday shopping season saw a surge in consumer spending, reflecting the booming post-war economy.
